wikipedia_page.main: Sir Andrew Ryan  (5 November 1876 – 31 December 1949) was a British diplomat. He was Consul-General to Morocco from 1924 to 1930, Minister to Saudi Arabia from 1930 to 1936,  and Consul-General to Albania from 1936 to 1939.He was the father of the Roman Catholic theologian and philosopher Columba Ryan and cartoonist John Ryan.
